President Donald Trump. (Evan Vucci, AP) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Washington &mdash; President Donald Trump has signed into law a bill that adds exploration of Mars as a Nasa goal. The new law also authorises $19.5bn in space agency funding for the 2017 budget year, which began October 1. Trump recently sent Congress a budget proposal that authorises $19.1bn for the space agency next year.The measure amends current law to add human exploration of Mars as one of Nasa's objectives. It also directs Nasa to manage human space flight programmes to help humans explore Mars and other destinations.Trump signed the bill in the Oval Office surrounded by astronauts and bill sponsors, including Senators Ted Cruz, R-Texas and Marco Rubio, R-Fla. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.